# .gitignore — Go / WASM project
#
# Based on GitHub's official Go template plus adjustments for the IoTMaker
# IDE layout (WASM binary output, local SQLite DB, user-uploaded files,
# WASM test runner support files if copied into the repo).

# ── Go build artefacts ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Binaries compiled directly (no .exe extension on Unix).
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib

# Test binaries built by `go test -c`.
*.test

# Output of the go coverage tool.
*.out
coverage.out
coverage.html

# Go workspace file (generally not committed — see go help work).
go.work
go.work.sum

# Dependency directories — we use modules, vendor/ is almost never committed.
vendor/

# ── WASM build output ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# The compiled WASM binary at the repository root (produced by make wasm /
# make wasm-force). The canonical copy lives under server/public/ide/ and
# is served to the browser; the root copy is an intermediate artefact.
main.wasm

# Do NOT ignore server/public/ide/main.wasm — that one IS served to the
# browser and its presence is required for `docker compose up` to serve
# the IDE without a prior wasm build. Keep it committed OR rebuild it in
# every deploy pipeline, your call.
# If you prefer to NEVER commit wasm (relying on build pipeline), uncomment:
# server/public/ide/main.wasm

# ── Runtime data (local dev) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

# SQLite development database and WAL/SHM sidecar files.
server/data/iotmaker.db
server/data/iotmaker.db-journal
server/data/iotmaker.db-wal
server/data/iotmaker.db-shm

# User-uploaded project files (code, images, docs) — never commit these.
server/data/files/

# Redis dump if someone runs redis locally with persistence.
dump.rdb

# ── Logs & local scratch ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────

*.log
/tmp/
/.tmp/

# ── IDE / editor files ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# VS Code.
.vscode/
*.code-workspace

# JetBrains (GoLand / IntelliJ).
.idea/
*.iml
*.ipr
*.iws

# Vim.
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# Emacs.
\#*\#
.\#*

# Sublime.
*.sublime-project
*.sublime-workspace

# ── OS files ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# macOS.
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride
Icon?
._*

# Linux.
.directory
.Trash-*

# Windows.
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
Desktop.ini
$RECYCLE.BIN/

# ── Secrets / environment ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Never commit env files with credentials. A sample template like .env.example
# CAN be committed — it has placeholders, not real secrets.
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
*.pem
*.key

# ── Node (wasm test runner uses node, but deps should not be committed) ───────

node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# ── Project-specific ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# utilWasm/ contains go_js_wasm_exec and wasm_exec.js copied from a Go
# toolchain for running WASM tests. The files are small and the project
# may intentionally vendor them to avoid Go-version path fragility
# (lib/wasm vs misc/wasm across Go versions). Keep them committed —
# they are NOT ignored. Delete this comment block if you decide otherwise.

# Screenshots and scratch images dropped into the root during debugging.
/screenshot-*.png
/screen-*.png
/tmp-*.png

# Docker build/local overrides (docker-compose.override.yml is a common
# local-only customisation file).
docker-compose.override.yml

# Goreleaser output if ever used.
dist/

CLAUDE.menu.md
_CLAUDE.md
lixo.txt
utilsZipFile/*.zip
/IA
CLAUDE*
INVARIANTS.md
